{"comments":"TextVariant - typographic case variants beyond simple transforms.\n\nWhile TextTransform changes case at render time, TextVariant uses\nOpenType features to access variant glyphs designed for specific uses:\n\n- **SmallCaps**: Uppercase forms at lowercase height\n- **AllSmallCaps**: All letters as small capitals\n- **PetiteCaps**: Even smaller capitals (between x-height and cap-height)\n- **AllPetiteCaps**: All letters as petite capitals\n- **Unicase**: Mixed uppercase/lowercase forms\n- **TitlingCaps**: Capitals optimized for large display sizes\n\n## Why variants matter\n\nSmall capitals are not simply \"shrunk uppercase\" — they are distinct\nglyphs with adjusted stroke weights to match the visual weight of\nlowercase letters. A proper small-cap 'A' has thicker strokes than\na regular 'A' reduced to the same height.\n\n## CSS Mapping\n\nMaps to `font-variant-caps` and related OpenType features.\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[64,15],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TextVariant.purs","start":[64,3]},"title":"CapsNormal"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[65,14],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TextVariant.purs","start":[65,3]},"title":"SmallCaps"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[66,17],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TextVariant.purs","start":[66,3]},"title":"AllSmallCaps"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[67,15],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TextVariant.purs","start":[67,3]},"title":"PetiteCaps"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[68,18],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TextVariant.purs","start":[68,3]},"title":"AllPetiteCaps"},